1
00:00:01,339 --> 00:00:02,685
Let's go see Great-Grandma!

2
00:00:02,693 --> 00:00:03,693
"Ee-Grandma"?

3
00:00:03,713 --> 00:00:04,921
It's Great-Grandma!

4
00:00:04,961 --> 00:00:07,121
I've been saying
"Ee-Grandma" this whole time!

5
00:00:07,161 --> 00:00:08,821
It's Great-Grandma!

6
00:00:08,861 --> 00:00:09,921
Ee-Grandma.

7
00:00:09,961 --> 00:00:12,863
I said it's Great-Grandma!

8
00:00:14,692 --> 00:00:16,247
Great-Grandma, hello!

9
00:00:16,287 --> 00:00:17,672
It's Great-Grandma!

10
00:00:17,712 --> 00:00:19,520
I said it's Ee-Grandma!

11
00:00:19,819 --> 00:00:21,640
Ugh, let's go over there.

12
00:00:21,757 --> 00:00:23,000
Oh, a dead body!

13
00:00:23,044 --> 00:00:24,369
Dead body!

14
00:00:24,417 --> 00:00:27,863
Dead body! Ready, set—
dead body, dead body!

15
00:00:27,903 --> 00:00:30,960
Don't say "dead body"!
Say "the departed"!

16
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,550
The departed, the departed!

17
00:00:33,590 --> 00:00:35,436
- It's a zombie!
- Whoa, a zombie!

18
00:00:38,325 --> 00:00:39,516
Watch out, zombie!

19
00:00:39,556 --> 00:00:41,960
Hey, you kids behaving
yourselves?

20
00:00:44,086 --> 00:00:46,332
Ah, hello everyone.
Sorry to keep you waiting.

21
00:00:46,650 --> 00:00:48,880
Thank you for everything.

22
00:00:49,729 --> 00:00:50,960
Ah, hello, hello.

23
00:00:51,187 --> 00:00:52,697
You met him yesterday too?

24
00:00:52,699 --> 00:00:53,868
We run into each other daily.

25
00:00:53,908 --> 00:00:55,359
Every day?

26
00:00:55,514 --> 00:00:56,623
Hey there!

27
00:00:56,663 --> 00:00:58,520
Thanks so much for today!

28
00:00:58,550 --> 00:01:00,000
It's Ramo!

29
00:01:00,072 --> 00:01:01,610
Mama, wait wait wait.

30
00:01:01,842 --> 00:01:03,640
Things are so gloomy over here.

31
00:01:04,842 --> 00:01:06,044
Sorry about that.

32
00:01:06,084 --> 00:01:07,322
- You okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

33
00:01:07,362 --> 00:01:09,433
- Don't push yourself.
- Thanks.

34
00:01:11,163 --> 00:01:12,410
Did everyone see her?

35
00:01:12,450 --> 00:01:14,370
Grandma looked so peaceful,
like she was sleeping.

36
00:01:14,410 --> 00:01:16,229
Just totally at rest, you know?

37
00:01:17,109 --> 00:01:18,881
She's not sleeping.

38
00:01:18,917 --> 00:01:21,560
Don't go pushing it on people.

39
00:01:24,169 --> 00:01:27,582
What the— Uncle, just go
get changed already.

40
00:01:27,622 --> 00:01:28,920
Wait, he's drinking?

41
00:01:29,108 --> 00:01:30,394
Oh yeah, he's drinking.

42
00:01:30,434 --> 00:01:32,316
- Oh, come on.
- He's always drinking.

43
00:01:32,356 --> 00:01:33,881
Stop him!

44
00:01:33,921 --> 00:01:35,280
I can't stop him.

45
00:01:39,151 --> 00:01:41,351
Alright!

46
00:01:45,207 --> 00:01:47,244
Ta-da!

47
00:01:47,284 --> 00:01:48,637
Yay!

48
00:01:48,663 --> 00:01:50,106
Thank you.

49
00:01:52,799 --> 00:01:54,506
Here we go!

50
00:02:01,805 --> 00:02:05,041
- Shall we have some action tonight?
- I'm so glad to be alive!

51
00:02:31,987 --> 00:02:34,187
I Still Want to Do It with My Wife

52
00:02:36,252 --> 00:02:38,452
Episode 8: Wife VS Mother

53
00:03:17,183 --> 00:03:19,758
He's always been like that.
He can't help it at times like those.

54
00:03:19,798 --> 00:03:21,219
I can't help laughing.

55
00:03:21,259 --> 00:03:23,365
Yeah, at Grandpa's funeral too.

56
00:03:23,405 --> 00:03:25,098
I seriously thought I'd die.

57
00:03:25,138 --> 00:03:26,610
You laughed way too much.

58
00:03:27,533 --> 00:03:29,801
Well, keeping busy.

59
00:03:30,096 --> 00:03:31,710
Oh, like TV dramas?

60
00:03:31,750 --> 00:03:34,203
Well, some stuff I can't talk about yet.

61
00:03:34,243 --> 00:03:35,840
Was the last one a reenactment show?

62
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:39,046
Yeah. Reenactment shows... I do those too.

63
00:03:39,086 --> 00:03:41,303
- Oh, you do those.
- How's the pay?

64
00:03:45,359 --> 00:03:49,785
Well, it's a tough profession. Acting...

65
00:03:50,013 --> 00:03:54,400
Hey, I might be able
to introduce you to Kiichi Nakai.

66
00:03:54,628 --> 00:03:58,980
My classmate's brother knows him,
or maybe it's his brother.

67
00:03:59,020 --> 00:04:00,310
Nakai's.

68
00:04:00,493 --> 00:04:05,100
Nah, it's fine. Besides,
I'm a screenwriter, not an actor.

69
00:04:05,140 --> 00:04:09,920
What're you saying? Acting, screenwriting,
it's all the same thing!

70
00:04:10,353 --> 00:04:14,560
Right, bro? Hey, how long
are you gonna keep crying?

71
00:04:15,084 --> 00:04:19,045
Don't you feel sad at all?

72
00:04:19,408 --> 00:04:21,879
Mom died, you know!

73
00:04:21,919 --> 00:04:24,800
Can't help it. It was her time.

74
00:04:25,701 --> 00:04:30,933
Hey, Chika. You must want this guy
to get his act together soon, right?

75
00:04:30,973 --> 00:04:33,041
No, he's seriously hopeless.

76
00:04:33,081 --> 00:04:37,480
He has no work, and he's bad at socializing,
so he never meets anyone.

77
00:04:37,552 --> 00:04:42,540
Oh, that's not true. He was a bright,
lovely boy... back in elementary school.

78
00:04:42,580 --> 00:04:44,200
Elementary school? That was ages ago.

79
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,980
Here we go! Fight!

80
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:49,017
Hey, stop egging them on. Just don't.

81
00:04:49,057 --> 00:04:51,089
Anyway, Chika,

82
00:04:51,129 --> 00:04:57,086
It's your job to nurture Gota's talent.
It's all he's got.

83
00:04:57,126 --> 00:04:59,179
Huh? You really think so?

84
00:04:59,219 --> 00:05:02,713
Of course. You're the one
who saw it in him.

85
00:05:02,733 --> 00:05:04,560
Enough of that, Mom.

86
00:05:05,232 --> 00:05:07,695
He don't look talented to me.

87
00:05:07,735 --> 00:05:09,686
He went to Kita High, right?

88
00:05:10,092 --> 00:05:11,320
The idiot school.

89
00:05:11,867 --> 00:05:14,200
Test scores don't matter.

90
00:05:14,346 --> 00:05:19,087
Can we drop this? Please.
This is Grandma's funeral.

91
00:05:19,127 --> 00:05:22,636
Forget it, I'm leaving.

92
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,160
See? He ran away.

93
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:28,882
Well, of course he did.
You're not kind to him.

94
00:05:28,922 --> 00:05:30,319
Are you drinking?

95
00:05:30,359 --> 00:05:31,886
That guy's hopeless.

96
00:05:32,260 --> 00:05:33,279
- Right?
- Hopeless.

97
00:05:33,319 --> 00:05:35,422
That's exactly why
he's such a lost cause.

98
00:05:35,462 --> 00:05:37,975
Yanagida Family Waiting Room

99
00:05:39,210 --> 00:05:41,157
Yanagida Family Ceremony Hall

100
00:05:41,197 --> 00:05:43,403
Sachiko Yanagida Funeral Hall

101
00:05:43,422 --> 00:05:46,782
Wake: Oct. 12 from 7 PM
Funeral: Oct. 13 10-11 AM

102
00:06:04,894 --> 00:06:08,133
Huh? I didn't know you smoked.

103
00:06:08,779 --> 00:06:12,634
No, I quit already.

104
00:06:12,719 --> 00:06:15,652
It's just suffocating in there.

105
00:06:19,293 --> 00:06:21,760
Must be tough for you too, Go.

106
00:06:22,719 --> 00:06:27,923
Yeah... It's not easy.

107
00:06:30,437 --> 00:06:32,280
Chika seems pretty strong-willed.

108
00:06:35,309 --> 00:06:38,423
It's hard to make a living
in that line of work, right?

109
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,785
Yeah.

110
00:06:44,433 --> 00:06:49,480
Not that a twice-divorced woman
should be worrying about others.

111
00:06:52,007 --> 00:06:57,687
My same-age cousin Kimiko
had a crush on me as kids.

112
00:07:00,976 --> 00:07:03,363
How've you been lately, Kimiko?

113
00:07:05,286 --> 00:07:09,160
Absolutely nothing going on.

114
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:12,920
Just living lonely with my cat.

115
00:07:20,906 --> 00:07:23,800
Life never goes the way you want.

116
00:07:25,685 --> 00:07:29,805
Then again, I'm not even sure
what I wanted in the first place.

117
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:43,400
Why are you staring at me?

118
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:46,480
No, I'm not.

119
00:07:50,773 --> 00:07:52,015
Hey,

120
00:07:55,169 --> 00:07:56,560
wanna kiss?

121
00:07:58,670 --> 00:07:59,943
Huh?

122
00:08:02,010 --> 00:08:03,563
We did it before, remember?

123
00:08:03,762 --> 00:08:05,470
Back in middle school.

124
00:08:11,127 --> 00:08:13,481
Yeah, we did.

125
00:08:15,926 --> 00:08:20,280
That was the best kiss
of my entire life.

126
00:08:22,820 --> 00:08:24,080
Seriously?

127
00:08:27,405 --> 00:08:28,820
Seriously.

128
00:08:38,396 --> 00:08:39,920
"Wanna kiss?"

129
00:08:40,857 --> 00:08:47,797
Every word from that line on was fantasy,
but the middle school kiss was real.

130
00:08:50,923 --> 00:08:53,093
What are you grinning about?

131
00:08:53,183 --> 00:08:54,520
Sorry.

132
00:08:56,083 --> 00:09:01,160
What kind of life would've
been the one we wanted?

133
00:09:04,557 --> 00:09:07,640
Well, at least you have someone.
That counts for something.

134
00:09:08,929 --> 00:09:11,640
Sometimes I get
overwhelmed by loneliness.

135
00:09:27,514 --> 00:09:31,356
Hey! Gota! Gota!
Where the hell are ya?!

136
00:09:31,396 --> 00:09:32,840
Huh? What?

137
00:09:32,844 --> 00:09:34,103
Get over here!

138
00:09:34,143 --> 00:09:37,023
Chika and your mom went at it!
It's a total disaster!

139
00:09:37,063 --> 00:09:38,122
W-What do you mean?

140
00:09:38,162 --> 00:09:39,538
Just hurry up!

141
00:09:39,578 --> 00:09:44,547
We need a referee! Joe Higuchi!
Or Mr. Takahashi!

142
00:09:44,703 --> 00:09:46,041
Off you go.

143
00:09:46,081 --> 00:09:47,640
Go! Now!

144
00:09:58,676 --> 00:10:02,920
I'm doing everything right!
I'm trying my hardest!

145
00:10:03,530 --> 00:10:05,835
I work full-time, do all the
housework and childcare,

146
00:10:05,875 --> 00:10:09,241
and support your precious
40-something kept man!

147
00:10:09,281 --> 00:10:11,563
I even help him with his work
on top of everything!

148
00:10:11,603 --> 00:10:13,647
What more do you want from me?!

149
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:18,433
I know that. You're doing a fine job,
I understand.

150
00:10:18,536 --> 00:10:22,040
But can't you be
a little kinder to him?

151
00:10:22,070 --> 00:10:28,883
It's simple, isn't it? Even Masashi Sada
sings about it. "Just love him."

152
00:10:28,967 --> 00:10:33,936
It's not simple at all. There's nothing
about him that makes me want to be kind.

153
00:10:33,976 --> 00:10:36,943
And that song would be totally
problematic by today's standards.

154
00:10:36,983 --> 00:10:42,320
Well, I have issues with today's values too.
I hate them.

155
00:10:43,063 --> 00:10:45,343
You just haven't updated
your thinking.

156
00:10:46,130 --> 00:10:47,710
What? What's going on?

157
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:51,729
Oh, good timing. We were just
talking about you, right, Chika?

158
00:10:51,769 --> 00:10:54,480
You mean telling me
to have sex with your son?

159
00:10:55,097 --> 00:10:56,710
What do you mean?
What happened?

160
00:10:56,750 --> 00:11:01,070
Cut it out! This is a funeral!
My mother's funeral!

161
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:03,723
Come on, kids, let's go over there.
Grab your games.

162
00:11:08,910 --> 00:11:13,970
Chika, give it another fifteen years
and you'll understand.

163
00:11:14,409 --> 00:11:17,720
Imagine Taro's wife
saying terrible things about him.

164
00:11:17,893 --> 00:11:22,560
You'd want to say something to her too.
You'd probably slap her, wouldn't you?

165
00:11:22,956 --> 00:11:26,440
Well, I can't really say
about something that far off.

166
00:11:26,570 --> 00:11:31,289
Besides, if Taro were a kept man past 40
like your son, I'd slap him instead.

167
00:11:31,329 --> 00:11:35,590
Right. You don't seem like the type
to take your own son's side. I can tell.

168
00:11:35,630 --> 00:11:40,215
Wait, hold on! What happened?
What is this fight about?!

169
00:11:40,255 --> 00:11:43,280
Why don't you ask
your precious Mama?

170
00:11:44,773 --> 00:11:46,725
This family is seriously messed up.

171
00:11:47,159 --> 00:11:48,600
Let go of me!

172
00:11:53,908 --> 00:11:59,200
What a piece of work.
Screaming like that at a time like this.

173
00:12:00,789 --> 00:12:02,965
How did it come to this?

174
00:12:03,973 --> 00:12:05,640
What did you say to her?

175
00:12:06,297 --> 00:12:10,640
I just told her to take good care
of you. What's wrong with that?

176
00:12:11,590 --> 00:12:12,960
Everything!

177
00:12:14,165 --> 00:12:19,000
Why? I'm your mother.
Of course I'd worry about you, right?

178
00:12:19,037 --> 00:12:28,000
Just stop it, Mama! Stop meddling
in our marriage all the time!

179
00:12:28,142 --> 00:12:30,320
Chika is doing her best!

180
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,840
No, she's not.

181
00:12:33,271 --> 00:12:37,160
That girl is not on your side.
I saw it clearly today.

182
00:12:37,609 --> 00:12:41,800
Divorce her. I told you
to let go of your attachments.

183
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:48,000
How can you just say that?!
What if she actually leaves me?!

184
00:12:48,020 --> 00:12:52,720
Who's gonna support me then?
Who?!

185
00:12:52,857 --> 00:12:56,520
Papa and Mama will live off pensions
eventually!

186
00:12:56,580 --> 00:13:02,200
But I'll starve to death! Starve!
What am I supposed to do?!

187
00:13:05,491 --> 00:13:10,440
I knew how pathetic I sounded,
but I couldn't stop myself.

188
00:13:10,724 --> 00:13:14,214
And what's wrong with
being attached to someone?!

189
00:13:14,364 --> 00:13:16,280
Of course I'm attached!

190
00:13:16,496 --> 00:13:21,480
She's stayed with a guy like me
all this time!

191
00:13:21,894 --> 00:13:26,455
I can't survive
without Chika!

192
00:13:26,495 --> 00:13:28,195
There's no one like her!

193
00:13:28,235 --> 00:13:35,205
That's why I have to make her happy,
even just once!

194
00:13:35,213 --> 00:13:38,194
I have to give her
something good in return!

195
00:13:38,324 --> 00:13:40,960
I... I... I...

196
00:13:41,724 --> 00:13:46,960
What? Gaping like a goldfish.
Then show her what you've got!

197
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:55,160
I didn't raise you to be like this!
Pathetic! What a disappointment!

198
00:13:56,965 --> 00:13:59,880
I know I'm a disappointment!

199
00:14:09,994 --> 00:14:12,710
Don't you laugh!
You're just as bad!

200
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:13,970
Yes, ma'am!

201
00:14:14,214 --> 00:14:19,630
He wasn't like this before...
Right, Papa?!

202
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:21,120
How should I know!

203
00:14:40,345 --> 00:14:43,965
Um, hey...

204
00:14:46,434 --> 00:14:53,165
It's not just attachment— okay,
maybe it is, but...

205
00:14:55,605 --> 00:14:57,760
what's so wrong with that?

206
00:14:58,907 --> 00:15:01,800
Even if it is, so what?

207
00:15:02,590 --> 00:15:05,760
It's because you're you, Chika.

208
00:15:06,133 --> 00:15:11,240
I... it's love. It's love.

209
00:15:12,581 --> 00:15:18,765
Um, probably... probably...
probably love.

210
00:15:55,737 --> 00:15:56,737
Gota, go!

211
00:15:56,739 --> 00:15:58,020
- You got this!
- Go, Gota!

212
00:15:58,060 --> 00:15:59,060
Come on! Come on!

213
00:15:59,064 --> 00:16:00,440
You can do it!

214
00:16:01,266 --> 00:16:02,712
What the hell?

215
00:16:02,752 --> 00:16:04,003
One week later

216
00:16:04,043 --> 00:16:06,840
Ew. Gross. That is so gross.

217
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:10,280
Yeah, I figured...

218
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:13,340
She hasn't said a word to me
since the funeral.

219
00:16:13,380 --> 00:16:15,640
No kidding. What do you expect?

220
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:18,956
If it were me, I'd have stabbed
your mother right then and there.

221
00:16:54,425 --> 00:16:55,920
Thanks for the food.

222
00:16:56,522 --> 00:17:04,240
I was scared. We'd gone days without
speaking after fights plenty of times,

223
00:17:04,414 --> 00:17:08,960
but Chika's anger this time
was clearly different.

224
00:17:09,577 --> 00:17:11,600
This was no longer just about me—

225
00:17:12,073 --> 00:17:19,080
I feared she'd completely given up on
my parents and the entire Yanagida family.

226
00:17:20,354 --> 00:17:24,086
Hey Mama, aren't you gonna eat
the food Papa made?

227
00:17:24,380 --> 00:17:28,680
Mama hasn't been feeling well
since the funeral.

228
00:17:29,180 --> 00:17:30,920
Oh, and my heart too.

229
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:33,981
Are you okay?

230
00:17:34,021 --> 00:17:35,021
No.

231
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:38,280
I'm not okay. Not okay at all.

232
00:17:38,838 --> 00:17:43,800
But thank you for worrying about me.
Hearing you say that helps a little.

233
00:17:45,775 --> 00:17:47,080
There, there.

234
00:18:09,144 --> 00:18:10,597
Get changed right after your bath.

235
00:18:10,637 --> 00:18:12,680
Okay. Got it.

236
00:18:15,068 --> 00:18:16,300
What?

237
00:18:16,430 --> 00:18:18,160
We need to talk tonight.

238
00:18:31,853 --> 00:18:38,200
The thought of finally being handed
an ultimatum terrified me beyond words.

239
00:19:15,952 --> 00:19:17,605
Um...

240
00:19:19,490 --> 00:19:20,760
I'm here.

241
00:19:21,245 --> 00:19:24,365
Cut that dramatic face.
It makes me sick.

242
00:19:25,387 --> 00:19:26,760
What's this about?

243
00:19:27,790 --> 00:19:29,040
Sit down.

244
00:19:30,474 --> 00:19:32,120
Sit down. Now.

245
00:19:45,113 --> 00:19:46,600
You. Produce results.

246
00:19:47,371 --> 00:19:48,371
Huh?

247
00:19:48,383 --> 00:19:49,640
Don't "huh" me.

248
00:19:51,211 --> 00:19:53,423
Wait, results?

249
00:19:53,463 --> 00:19:56,273
Results are results.
Need me to say it again?

250
00:19:56,468 --> 00:19:58,033
Results!

251
00:20:00,952 --> 00:20:03,416
Seriously, what do you
even think about all this?

252
00:20:04,380 --> 00:20:07,160
- About what?
- That woman, you idiot.

253
00:20:08,471 --> 00:20:09,720
Oh, my mom?

254
00:20:09,915 --> 00:20:11,503
Who the hell else?

255
00:20:12,914 --> 00:20:20,781
I mean, yeah, I think she was
out of line. I said something back then.

256
00:20:20,821 --> 00:20:24,836
"Said something" my ass. Why did I
have to put up with all that crap?

257
00:20:27,677 --> 00:20:31,800
I'm done with your family.
Never again.

258
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:37,996
I even considered divorce. But backing
down now doesn't sit right with me.

259
00:20:38,429 --> 00:20:42,603
She's the one who raised a loser
like you, but she blames it all on me.

260
00:20:42,970 --> 00:20:45,550
Just thinking about it makes
my blood boil all over again.

261
00:20:45,590 --> 00:20:46,906
What do you think about this?

262
00:20:46,946 --> 00:20:50,601
Like I said, I think
she was out of line.

263
00:20:50,641 --> 00:20:54,600
I told her off back then.
I lost my temper, okay?

264
00:20:54,604 --> 00:20:57,636
"Lost your temper"? If you're
gonna lose anything, lose ties with her.

265
00:21:01,291 --> 00:21:05,451
The only way to get back at that woman
is for you to produce results.

266
00:21:07,420 --> 00:21:09,800
You want results over something
like that?

267
00:21:10,324 --> 00:21:13,883
"Something like that"?! Do you have any
idea how much she hurt me?!

268
00:21:16,641 --> 00:21:20,329
But what do you mean by "results"?

269
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:25,741
Like, becoming a big
star? That's a bit...

270
00:21:25,872 --> 00:21:31,360
Shut up! Figure it out yourself!
You've got a shit-for-brains, don't you?!

271
00:21:31,959 --> 00:21:35,010
Well, my brain is shit,
that's why I can't think of anything...

272
00:21:35,050 --> 00:21:36,621
Shut it. That's not funny at all.

273
00:21:36,661 --> 00:21:39,230
You're the one who brought up
the shit-brain thing, Chika...

274
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:42,323
Shut up! Get lost! Scram!

275
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:57,120
But, I mean, results aren't exactly
something you can produce overnight...

276
00:21:59,770 --> 00:22:01,040
I'll try, though.

277
00:22:02,530 --> 00:22:06,000
Attachment, love,
all that talk...

278
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:11,880
None of it scared me nearly as much
as the word "results."

279
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:16,082
Next Episode Preview

280
00:22:16,122 --> 00:22:18,250
What's this?
"Comedy committee"?

281
00:22:18,290 --> 00:22:20,990
Taro's changed a bit, hasn't he?

282
00:22:21,030 --> 00:22:22,760
Just shut up and produce results.

283
00:22:22,870 --> 00:22:25,800
Sometimes you have to produce results
even if it kills you, right?

284
00:22:25,896 --> 00:22:29,933
If you don't produce results, I don't
know what'll happen to our marriage.
